## Routing & layout

- Routes constant: `Routes = { LANDING_PAGE: '/', PROJECTS: '/projects', CONTACT: '/contact' }`.
- Every page wraps content in `PageLayout` and passes a `Route`. `PageLayout` renders `PageHead` (SEO/canonical/hreflang/og) + `StickyHeader` (logo, nav, theme toggle, language switcher, mobile sidebar) + `<main>` + footer.
- SEO copy resolved via `useSeo(route)` reading i18n keys (`landingPage.*`, `projects.seo.*`, `contact.seo.*`).

## Theming

- `ThemeProviderCustom` (`src/context/ThemeContext.tsx`) holds `theme: 'dark' | 'light'`, persists to `localStorage`, sets `data-theme` on `<html>`. Renders `GlobalLoader` until mounted to avoid flash.
- CSS custom properties defined in `src/styles/globals.css` for both themes (`--primary`, `--bg-*`, `--text-*`, `--border-*`, `--hover-*`).
- MUI theme generated by `useMuiTheme()` from CSS-var-aware fallbacks in `src/utils/themeUtils.ts` (avoids first-paint lag).
- Token constants: `Themes`, `ColorTokens`, `breakpoints` in `src/constants/theme.ts`.

## Styling conventions

- `@use '@/styles/theme' as *;` exposes shadow/radius/breakpoints tokens.
- Mixins (`src/styles/mixins.scss`): `mq($name)` mobile-first max-width media query, `reduced-motion`, `text-gradient`, `primary-gradient`, `primary-border`, `section-glass-bg`, `card-glass-bg`, `floating-orb-base`, `top-accent-bar`, `card-hover`, `card-transition`, `card-padding`, `pulse-glow`, `orb-drift`, `float-y`, `rotate-spin`.
- Breakpoints: `xs 480, sm 768, md 1024, lg 1280, xl 1440` (also exposed in TS via `breakpoints`).
- Reusable wrapper: `Section` (alignment / background / shadow / border / gap / noPadding props). Use `Reveal` to wrap blocks for scroll-triggered fade-up/left/right via `IntersectionObserver`.

## Contact flow

1. `ContactForm` (uses `useRecaptchaV3({ action: 'contact_form_submit' })` + `useContactForm`).
2. `useRecaptchaV3` fetches site key from `/api/recaptcha/site-key`, loads `https://www.google.com/recaptcha/api.js`, executes token, then POSTs `{ token, action }` to `/api/recaptcha/verify`.
3. `/api/recaptcha/verify` validates with Google; enforces `RECAPTCHA_MIN_SCORE` (default `0.5`) and matching action.
4. On captcha success, `useContactForm` POSTs to `/api/contact/send` with `{ name, email, message, locale }`.
5. `/api/contact/send` (Resend) sends two emails: inquiry to `EmailAddresses.INFO`, confirmation to user. Confirmation copy localised via `getEmailConfirmationCopy(locale)` reading `public/locales/<locale>/email.json` with EN fallback.
6. Asset base URL for emails resolved via `getEmailAssetBaseUrl()` (env: `EMAIL_ASSET_BASE_URL` or `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL`, falling back to `SITE_URL`; rejects localhost).

## i18n conventions

- Use `useTranslation()` (no namespace arg) and pass full key paths to `t(...)`.
- For markup-in-translation (e.g. highlighted spans), use `<Trans i18nKey="..." components={{ highlight: <span /> }} />`.
- `Trans` is also used to inject `<highlight>` spans in `tagline` and project descriptions.
- Locale switching done by `LanguageSwitcher` calling `router.push(pathname, asPath, { locale })`.
- Adding a locale: extend `SUPPORTED_LOCALES` in `src/constants/locales.ts`, add `LOCALE_LABELS`, add flag in `LanguageSwitcher`, add `OG_LOCALE` mapping in `PageHead`, add `public/locales/<code>/{common,email}.json`.

## Projects page

- Data lives in `src/constants/projects.ts` (`Project`, `ProjectStatus`, `Screenshot`, `TechCategory`, `ProjectFeature`).
- Each project has a `projectKey` used as the i18n root: `projects.data.<projectKey>.{tagline,description,highlights,architectureSnapshot,keyProps,techCategories.*,features.*.{label,description}}`.
- Project logos may be theme-aware (`logoLight`/`logoDark`) â€” both `<Image>`s rendered, CSS toggles via `[data-theme]`.
- `ScreenshotCarousel` shows screenshots with optional `subtitle` overlay, browser-chrome frame, auto-advance (5 s), pause on hover/focus, dots, arrows, progress bar, group chip, full keyboard support; keys use `screenshot.src` (not index).
- `ProjectShowcase` panels in order: header (logo/title, status chip, open-source chip, CTAs, tagline, key prop pills) â†’ carousel â†’ Engineering Highlights â†’ Architecture Snapshot â†’ Tech Stack (`TechBadge` chips) â†’ Key Features.

## Constants worth knowing

- `EmailAddresses` (PascalCase const, plural) in `src/constants/rene.ts`: `INFO`, `ADMIN`, `NOREPLY`, `RENE` at `renekrajnc.com`.
- `skills` and `workExperiences` in `src/constants/rene.ts` (work experience IDs: `equaleyes`, `margento`, `direct4me`).
- `MaintenanceReasons`, `Themes`, `ColorTokens`, `Routes` follow the project's literal-union pattern: PascalCase plural const, singular type alias.

## Environment variables

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL`, `RECAPTCHA_SITE_KEY`, `RECAPTCHA_SECRET_KEY`, `RECAPTCHA_MIN_SCORE` (optional).
- `RESEND_API_KEY`, `RESEND_FROM_EMAIL` (optional), `RESEND_FROM_NAME` (optional), `EMAIL_ASSET_BASE_URL` (optional).

## Cross-cutting code conventions

See `code-conventions.mdc` and `git-and-changelog.mdc`. Highlights:

- Arrow functions everywhere (components, handlers, utilities).
- No `any` / `!` / untyped casts; centralise literal unions with `as const` and derive types.
- Avoid narrating comments â€” comment only non-obvious intent.
- Update `CHANGELOG.md` only under `## [Unreleased]` when prompted.
